@startuml AC-04_JWT_Alg_None_Bypass

title AC-04 — JWT alg:none Signature Bypass Grants Arbitrary Identity\nSTRIDE: Spoofing | Severity: Critical | Mitigation: M-04

left to right direction

skinparam usecase {
  BackgroundColor<< abuse >> #FFCCCC
  BorderColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  FontColor<< abuse >> #CC0000
  BackgroundColor<< normal >> #DDEEFF
  BorderColor<< normal >> #336699
}
skinparam actorBackgroundColor #EEF
skinparam actorBorderColor #336699
skinparam noteFontSize 10

actor "Registered User\n(any role)" as user #DDEEFF
actor "External Attacker\n(any valid account)" as attacker #FFCCCC

rectangle "VendNet System" {
  usecase "Authenticate with\nValid Signed JWT" as UC4 << normal >>
  usecase "Obtain Legitimate\nCustomer JWT" as AC4a << abuse >>
  usecase "Forge Unsigned JWT\n(alg:none) with ADMINISTRATOR Role" as AC4 << abuse >>
  usecase "Access All Admin Endpoints\nWithout Credentials" as AC4b << abuse >>
}

user --> UC4

attacker --> AC4a
AC4a ..> AC4  : <<enables>>
AC4 ..> UC4   : <<threatens>>
AC4 ..> AC4b  : <<extends>>

note right of AC4
  **Preconditions:**
  • Attacker can register any valid account
  • JWT library does not explicitly reject
    alg:none algorithm
  • No fixed expected-algorithm enforcement
    before signature verification
  • Admin endpoints protected only by
    JWT role-claim (no IP/session binding)
end note

note right of AC4b
  **Impact:**
  Confidentiality: full user table PII,
  BCrypt hashes, audit logs exfiltrated
  Integrity: roles reassigned, pricing
  modified, backdoor accounts created
  Business: complete system compromise,
  no physical access required,
  GDPR breach notification obligation
end note

note bottom of attacker
  **Attack vector:**
  1. Decode original HS256 JWT
  2. Change header: {"alg":"none","typ":"JWT"}
  3. Change payload role: "ADMINISTRATOR"
  4. Reconstruct with empty signature:
     base64(header).base64(payload).
end note

@enduml
